args: Akaw! You nailed a fish swimmin'\nthrough the water like it was nothing!\nMy dude, you are a LEGEND.
The key is attuning yourself to your prey's\nbreath. Match it, and you will strike true—\nno matter how fiercely the water rages.
I still don't have a clue what you're goin'\non about, but I appreciate you, bro!\nEven my cats are amped!
Heh. I used to share the fish I caught\nwith Mineuchi like this, too.
Man, this Mineuchi musta been\nlike family to you—just like these\nlittle party animals are to me.
Huh? You gettin' antsy again already?\nHey, sorry to ask, but would you take\nmy little guys out on the water again?
I see... Very well, then. Hold on tight.
Phew. That ought to do it for today.
You have a righteous day out there,\nlittle guy? Gah ha ha!
And hey, thanks again, bro.\nI owe you one.
Think nothing of it. It is enjoyable for both\nof us. That cat really is your Mineuchi.
Wait, what? I thought you said\nMineuchi was an all-black cat.
I speak figuratively—of the\nrelationship the two of you share.\nMineuchi was irreplaceable to me.

We would share the fish we caught in the
morning, spend the afternoon gazing at the
breaking waves, and huddle together as we
counted the stars in the night sky.
Our days spent living in harmony with the\nocean feel like they were only yesterday.
Even so, our companionship was\npredicated upon more than a mutual love\nof the beach. Only... I didn't realize it.

I poured my heart into my training,
ignorant of how much I valued him,
and then before I knew it, our paths
had diverged.
It was only when I lost him that I at last\nrealized just how much he meant to me.
Perhaps Mineuchi sensed that I took his\npresence for granted, devoted as I was to\nmy training. In a word, I was unworthy.
I failed to be for Mineuchi what you are\nfor those cats.

Listen, bro. I dunno your whole life story,
but here's the thing about cats—
they decide for themselves exactly
where they wanna be and when.
And if that Mineuchi of yours is alive,\nI'm sure he's out there livin' his best life.
The cat chose to be with you, and then\nchose to set off in search of new horizons.\nThat's not on you, my dude.
I do not search for Mineuchi solely\nbecause I feel responsible for his fate.\nI will find him—

And then what? You're gonna yank him
outta his new life and bring him back
home to you? You really think that's
gonna make him happy?

Look, bro. I can tell you ain't the kinda
guy who goes around messin' with
cats and their happiness.
...Unlike those mental dudes from before.
You let slip something about them earlier.\nOf whom do you speak?
Just a couple of bennies some rich dude\nhired out. They heard the rumors about\nsurfing cats and showed up to sniff around.

They didn't know the first thing about my
furry friends, but they tried to take 'em
away just the same. They're the punks who
raked me over and messed up my leg.
Have they come back since then?
Not since you showed up. If I had to guess,\nthey're probably stayin' in line since they\ncan tell you ain't some ordinary grom.
Good. May it remain that way.
I mean, I'm pretty sure you'd be fine\neven if they DID try to mess with you.\nJust keep your eyes peeled, yeah?
